modules.description: Extracts a name from a location structure, performs M4 macro escaping on strings, and reads and parses input into a structured suite representation. Operates on location records, strings, and a suite data type. Used to process source files with macro support and generate structured output for further analysis.

Converts specific domain types such as location, action, check, and check_output to their string representations, enabling readable logging and debugging. Handles structured data like check records, action lists, and test suites for detailed output generation. Used to format execution results and test configurations in a human-readable form.

Provides access to version strings, optional commit hashes, and optional commit dates. Works with strings and optional values representing build metadata. Used to embed build information in applications for debugging and tracking deployments.

Processes m4 macro expansions and executes test cases from GNU Autoconf test suites. Operates on structured test data, including test scripts and macro definitions. Enables automated execution of legacy test environments with modern runtime support.

Processes source files with macro support, converting them into structured suites while handling location-based name extraction and M4 escaping. Converts domain-specific data—such as actions, checks, and locations—into human-readable formats for logging and debugging. Retrieves build metadata including version strings, commit hashes, and dates for deployment tracking. Can generate structured output from source code, format test execution results, and embed build details into application outputs.
